This is a Python implementation of the classic card game **Blackjack**, developed as part of the **100 Days of Code** challenge.

The player competes against the dealer (computer) to get as close to 21 points as possible without exceeding it. The game follows standard Blackjack rules.

## ğŸš€ Features

- Player vs. dealer gameplay
- Basic Blackjack rules, including card value calculation and bust checking
- Option to 'Hit' or 'Stand' during the game
- Automatically ending the game when the dealer reaches 17 or higher

